  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promoting Human Security in Ruzizi Valley / Reconstruction programme Burundi, DR Congo / 2012-2016</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ZOA proposes this Promoting Human Security in Ruzizi Valley Programme, to enhance stability and security in the border area between Burundi and the DRC as preconditions for people to rebuild their lives and livelihoods and contribute to structural poverty reduction. The programme will contribute to legitimate government, build local government capacity and will create a visible peace dividend.</narrative>
  </description>
  <participating-org activity-id="NL-1-PPR-24342" ref="XM-DAC-7" role="1" type="10">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Dutch Ministry of Foreign Affairs (DGIS)</narrative>
  </participating-org>
  <activity-status code="4"></activity-status>
  <activity-date iso-date="2012-11-14" type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project received initial approval by the Ministry of Foreign Affairs on 28th June 2012 for a total amount of 60% of the proposed budget at the time of submission in March 2012. ZOA was then asked to submit a revised project plan by latest 15th September 2012. The Ministry notified ZOA of the approval of the revised plan on 16th November 2012, after which ZOA started implementation of the project. ZOA found it best to not start the revised project immediately after submission in September 2012 so not to run the risk of beginning project work on a wrong footing, we considered the operational risks of starting the project without having received the donor&#x2019;s ultimate directions, too high. Therefore, we could only start full project preparations in second half of November.</narrative>
  </activity-date>
